reviews.review: Decent for a casual movie goer, but as an ending to a series dating back to the 70s....it should have been much better, with a very anti-climatic ending to an overall boring film.
It was just ok to me. I feel like there was a lot of unnecessary people and things in the movie.

A pointless poorly written movie unworthy of the Star wars franchise.  Macguffin hunting stereotypes collect cliches without any significant risk or consequences.
Solutions to problems are pulled out of thin air in a way that makes us feel more like Star Trek than Star Wars.
This is not only the worst Star Wars movie I have ever seen it is the worst sci-fi movie I have ever seen.
Seriously don't waste your time.
Best movie of the series! Like always the critics are saying the opposite of the real people who can just enjoy a movie.

Much improved over the last Jedi, it’s not perfect and that’s fine. it wraps up the Skywalker saga and there is a lot of fan service which as someone who saw the original as a kid and still enjoys Star Wars the highs and lows alike makes me feel like a kid again .. don’t listen to the so called critics .. see it and form your own opinion

Rather than explore the fresh direction set up in the VIII, the script chose to spend its time jerking off the angrier parts of its fanbase.

It was fine for what it was, but it shouldn't be mistaken with a good movie.

Exceeded my expectations, but my expectations were low. Entertaining in a way you'll forget by next year. Story is a mess and has many missed opportunities. There is no emotional attachment to Rey after two movies, and so her scenes lack punch. Daisy Ridley mails in her performances when it comes to the physical acting. The whole thing has it moments, but mostly it falls short.

It stated off rather choppy and disjointed and I feared the worst, but I was pleasantly surprised by the action packed ending.  Thematically, a villain found redemption and the heroine found herself, so I thought it was a pretty upbeat note on which to end the nine movie series.  Of course, I doubt this will really be the final Star wars story if there is money to be made.
Over the past 42 years of the Star Wars franchise.  This movie summarizes the events from 1977 to 2019. They did an outstanding job putting this movie together!

I think the movie deserves a 70 but I'm rating 1 star to make a bigger impact. The movie was good if you suspend all logic and all the gravity of the previous Star Wars movies. The plot is dumb but at least it's entertaining. Wait until the movie comes out on Netflix. I wasn't going to see this and give Disney any money they don't deserve but my friend bought me tickets without my consent.
